article.headline: IUPUI 75, S. Utah 74
article.story: CEDAR CITY, Utah (AP) -- Austin Montgomery made a layup with 1.8 seconds left in overtime to give IUPUI a 75-74 win over Southern Utah on Thursday night. Montgomery picked up a loose ball in traffic and laid it in to lift the Jaguars (13-12, 6-5 Mid-Continent) the win and give him 30 points in the game. Gary Patterson scored 17 points for IUPUI, while Angelo Smith had 11 points and David Barlow added 10. Billy Pettiford grabbed 10 rebounds, as the Jaguars won the rebound battle 39-25. Steve Barnes, who forced overtime on a 3-pointer with 1.7 seconds left in regulation, led the Thunderbirds (15-11, 5-6) with 16 points and eight assists. Justin Allen scored 13 points, Tate Sorensen had 12, and Orlando Griego and Nurudeen Adepoju added 11 each, as all five Southern Utah starters finished in double figures. The Thunderbirds were down 55-41 with about 10 minutes left, then rallied and took the game to overtime tied at 69 on Barnes' 3-pointer.
